						               													<description>A strange word game, where each player draws from a bag 39 tiles with geometric segments on them.  Simultaneously, both players try to arrange their tiles to make a word of four or more letters (most letters are 2x3 tiles, the &amp;quot;I&amp;quot; is 1x3, &amp;quot;M&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;T&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;W&amp;quot;and &amp;quot;Y&amp;quot; are 3x3).  First player to shout Stop! wins the round and scores.  The word may be contested.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Note that a word with an &amp;quot;I&amp;quot; in it will score less, and conversely with &amp;quot;M&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;T&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;W&amp;quot; or &amp;quot;Y&amp;quot;.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The players swap boards and shuffle the tiles of each board around, then play repeats.  On the second round, swap again but draw 6 more tiles.  Words must now be 5+ letters.  Repeat for a third round (six-letter words), drawing six tiles again, so there are six words scored total in a game.  The boards show bonuses that can be scored by making really long words.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The rules show the exact patterns that make up each letter.  An incorrectly drawn letter will lose a challenge.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
